Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 Docker is an open platform for developing, shipping, and running applications. With Docker, you can separate your applications from your infrastructure and treat your infrastructure like a managed application. Docker helps you ship code faster, test faster, deploy faster, and shorten the cycle between writing code and running code.\
Docker does this by combining kernel containerization features with workflows and tooling that helps you manage and deploy your applications.\
Docker containers can be directly used in Kubernetes, which allows them to be run in the Kubernetes Engine with ease. After learning the essentials of Docker, you will have the skillset to start developing Kubernetes and containerized applications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa640\partightenfactor0

